 the location of that missing child The claimant did not contribute to the disappearance of the missing child The claimant was not related to the missing child at the time of recovery The claimant was not working for any organization either paid or volunteer involved in the recovery of missing persons Any person claiming a reward may submit only one claim form for each recovered missing child The CVCGC Board must receive the claim form no later than six months from the date the child was recovered Filing Claims Reward claims may be filed with the Government Claims Branch Requests for claim forms and brochures should be directed to the Government Claims Branch 1 800 955 3564 or 916 323 5768 For additional information on Missing Persons click on the link below http caag state ca us missing index htm California Attorney General s Office Missing Person s Home Page PageTop Back to Top of Page 2003 State of California use htm Conditions of Use Privacy htm Privacy Policy
